<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - CUMMINS ISM ENGINE - TROUBLESHOOTING - Vehicle Speed
        Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>When monitoring engine functions with an EST, if the vehicle is moving the miles-per-hour will display
                as MPH=XXX (actual vehicle speed if operating properly). To test the sensor and circuits to the ECM, use
                the following charts.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0827715">
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector (962) from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove
                    the sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer
                    gear, then back out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten lock nut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#8226;m). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly
                    for the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
            <para>Construct test leads using terminals (Navistar Part No. 1680205C1), short length of 16 gauge wire and
                alligator clips.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle. The jack may lower and serious injury
                        could result. Always support vehicle with floor jacks. Always block wheels to prevent vehicle
                        from moving.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>EXTREME CAUTION should be used to prevent personal injury resulting from contact with rotating
                        vehicle wheels when connecting test leads.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0827723" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.52in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Inspect VSS for damage and proper adjustment before performing this test. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827715">Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor
                                        (VSS)</hotlnk>above.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect engine harness (962) from VSS and use test leads to measure resistance
                                    between terminal 1 and 2 of sensor connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS, terminal 1 to 2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>600 to 800 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Measure resistance to ground at both sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS, term. 1 and 2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid personal contact with
                                    rotating vehicle wheels during test. Connect meter leads to test leads.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across
                                    the two sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS, across terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>>2.0 volts AC</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>VSS checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0827715">Inspecting And Adjusting The Vehicle Speed Sensor</hotlnk>
                                    (above).
                                    <emph type="bold">Note: Improper sensor adjustment will cause low, erratic or no
                                        output.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuits To ECM</title>
            <para>To check circuits between the ECM and the speedometer/tachometer unit, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08270_146.xml" xrefid="x0827716">ATA Data Link Connector (220) and
                    Speedometer/Tachometer Input Circuits</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <table id="t0827724" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuits To ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.55in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove connector (962) from vehicle speed sensor. Remove ECM connector (957) from
                                    the ECM and inspect. ECM harness connector and ECM pins OK?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace harness connector terminals if damaged. If ECM pins are damaged, have
                                    Cummins dealer replace ECM. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s08270_141.xml" xrefid="x0827705">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (957), use test leads and measure resistance to ground at terminals
                                    21 and 22 (circuits 97AJ and 97AK).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(957), 97AJ and 97AK to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K ohms, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (957), measure resistance between terminals 21 and 22 (circuits 97AJ
                                    and 97AK) and all other terminals in connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(957), 97AJ and 97AK and all others.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short circuit between circuits where resistance between terminals is less
                                    than 100K ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (957), measure voltage at terminals 21 and 22 (circuits 97AJ and
                                    97AK) to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(957), 97AJ and 97AK to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to unwanted voltage source in circuit where voltage at terminal is
                                    more than 1.5 volts, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (957) use test leads and jumper terminal 21 (circuit 97AJ) to ground.
                                    At connector (962) measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AJ.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(962), 97AJ to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AJ between connectors (957) and (962),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (957) use test leads and jumper terminal 22 (circuit 97AK) to ground.
                                    At connector (962) measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AK.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(962), 97AK to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AK between connectors (957) and (962),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>The vehicle speed sensor circuits between the sensor and ECM check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
